I still never thought I’d be on a tv show.. or even on tv like this to start with. I’d be lying if I said I wasn’t loving every single second of this experience but I’d also be lying if I said this was easy. I have a new found respect for actors now since we are one of the few shows to memorize all our scripts written on the same day, on a daily basis and with my fish memory “which is why they call me “Dori” you can all imagine the struggle lol . Then again Nothing good is ever easy but it’s almost always worth it ;) so never say no to a new adventure you never know what it has in store for you 🖤 I just hope you guys are loving it as much as me . P.s: I Always love reading your thoughts #grateful #fozaza #fozazastyle #mbctrending

Let me tell you something I’ve learned in my position over the years... being on social media or being public isn’t always fun but ohhhhhhh how rewarding it is when you let it teach you a few things and learn that ... you can’t let people scare you. You can’t go through your whole life trying to please everyone else... you can’t go through life worrying about what everyone is going to think... whether it’s your hair, clothes, what you have to say, how you feel, what you believe in or who you chose to love. You cannot let the judgement of others stop you from being you! Because if you do, your no longer you, your someone everyone else what’s you to be. And that would be a shame. ❤️ so what’s stopping you?
